- ## Scalability
#Scalability #Research #Challenges #Knowledge #Graphs 
Recent research efforts tried to address the problem of processing large RDF data by developing native RDF stores with SPARQL Protocol and RDF Query Language (SPARQL) endpoints (e.g., Jena, Seasme, RDF-3X). Nevertheless, the scalability of these systems is limited by their centralized architec- ture. To achieve better scalability, the Semantic Web community started investigating how to leverage big data processing frame- works to process large amounts of RDF data [20].
